  "text": "Animals were acclimatized and tested for mechanical and thermal sensitivity as previously described [CITATION_1] . Thermal sensitivity latencies from the six applications were used to calculate the mean latency per animal and mean latencies were combined to calculate group means. Mechanical sensitivity was measured twice (1 week apart) 2 weeks prior to sacrifice, and the two testing days were averaged together to give one total mechanical sensitivity value.",
